name: Triduana

attributes.attribute: pulled her eyes out of her head to avoid an unwanted suitor
possible local title of the goddess

sources: Monaghan, Patricia. The Encyclopedia of Celtic Mythology and Folklore. Checkmark Books, 2008.
text: Minor British goddess Triduana, who shares a similar tale with Ireland's Brigit, reportedly pulled her own eyes out of her head in order to evade an unwelcome suitor. It could be postulated that Triduana's appellation was a provincial epithet for the goddess, as Brigit was considered a triple goddess and the name Triduana possesses the syllable for "three."
